    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-07-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="106"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89Latvia/44a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-07-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 20, 1925</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 273</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to previous correspondence
                    regarding the indebtedness of Latvia to the United States, you are informed that
                    in a note dated June 26, 1925,<note n="52" xml:id="d106fn52">Not printed.</note>
                    the Latvian Minister at Washington <pb facs="0291" n="165" xml:id="pg_165"/>
                    informed the Department of his instructions to negotiate the debt funding
                    agreement and stated that he desired to enter into immediate discussions with
                    the World War Foreign Debt Commission. This information was communicated to the
                    Secretary of the Treasury and on July 8, 1925, Mr. Seya was introduced to Mr.
                    Winston, the Acting Secretary of the Treasury and the Secretary of the World War
                    Foreign Debt Commission, with a view to the inauguration of the negotiations in
                        question.<note n="53" xml:id="d106fn53">For negotiations and text of
                        agreement signed Sept. 24, 1925, see <hi rend="italic">Combined Annual
                            Reports of the World War Foreign Debt Commission</hi>, pp.
                        182–193.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Butler Wright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
